==English==
===Etymology===
{{wikipediapar|headbanging}}
From [[head]] + [[bang]] + [[-er]], referring to the dance move of shaking the head in time with the music.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-headbanger.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''headbanger'''
# One who dances by violently shaking the head in time to the music.
# By extension, one who enjoys [[heavy metal]] [[rock]] music, to which this sort of dance is usually performed.